Dense regular CT composes largely of collagen type I fibres arranged in parallel arrays;  imparts tensile strength     in one direction. There are relatively little GS, relatively fewer cells and cell types; cells that are present are largely fibroblasts (F). 
Dense regular CT can be seen in tendons     (below, A), aponeuroses (right, B)and ligaments     .
